#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:4
msgid "Standalone Player"
msgstr "Lecteur autonome"

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:6
msgid ""
"The standalone player allows a Blender game to be run without having to load "
"the Blender system. This allows games to be distributed to other users, "
"without their requiring a detailed knowledge of Blender (and also without "
"the possibility of unauthorized modification). Note that the Game Engine "
"Save as Runtime is an add-on facility which must be pre-loaded before use."
msgstr ""
"Le lecteur autonome permet à un jeu Blender de se lancer sans avoir à "
"charger le système Blender. Ceci permet la distribution des jeux à d'autres "
"utilisateurs, sans exiger une connaissance détaillée de Blender (et sans "
"possibilité de modification non autorisée). Notez que l'option *Save as "
"Runtime* du Moteur de jeu est un utilitaire add-on qui doit être préchargé "
"avant utilisation. "

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:13
msgid ""
"The following procedure will give a standalone version of a working game."
msgstr "La procédure suivante générera une version autonome du jeu."

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:15
msgid ""
":menuselection:`File --> User Preferences --> Add-ons --> Game Engine --> "
"Save As Game Engine Runtime` enable the checkbox. (You can also *Save User "
"Settings*, in which case the add-on will always be present whenever Blender "
"is re-loaded)."
msgstr ""
":menuselection:`File --> User Preferences --> Add-ons --> Game Engine --> "
"Save As Game Engine Runtime` cochez la case. (vous pouvez aussi utiliser "
"*Save User Settings*, auquel cas l'add-on sera toujours présent dès que "
"Blender est rechargé)."

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:19
msgid ""
":menuselection:`File --> Export --> Save As Game Engine Runtime` (give "
"appropriate directory/filename) confirm with *Save as Game Engine Runtime*."
msgstr ""
":menuselection:`File --> Export --> Save As Game Engine Runtime` (donne le "
"dossier/fichier approprié) confirmez avec *Save as Game Engine Runtime*."

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:22
msgid ""
"The game can then be executed by running the appropriate ``.exe`` file. Note "
"that all appropriate libraries are automatically loaded by the add-on."
msgstr ""
"Le fichier peut alors être exécuté en lançant le fichier ``.exe`` "
"correspondant. Notez que toutes les bibliothèques nécessaires sont "
"automatiquement chargées par l'add-on."

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:25
msgid ""
"If you are interested in licensing your game, read `Licensing <https://www."
"blender.org/about/license/>`__ for a discussion of the issues involved."
msgstr ""
"Si vous êtes intéressé par la licenciation de votre jeu, lisez `Licenciation "
"des jeux Blender <https://www.blender.org/about/license/>`__ pour une "
"discussion des problèmes inhérents."

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:29
msgid "Exporting..."
msgstr "Exporter..."

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:31
msgid ""
"If the game is to be exported to other computers, make a new empty directory "
"for the game runtime and all its ancillary libraries etc. Then make sure the "
"**whole** directory is transferred to the target computer"
msgstr ""
"Si le jeu doit être exporté sur d'autres ordinateurs, créez un nouveau "
"dossier vide pour le code du jeu et toutes ses bibliothèques supplémentaires "
"etc. Puis assurez-vous que **tout** le dossier est transféré sur "
"l'ordinateur cible."
